The paper deals with the problem of meta-mining, which involves recommending data mining workflows based on dataset and workflow descriptors. This problem has similarities with recommendation systems, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of semantic descriptions for algorithms, which is a topic studied in the sub-category of computer engineering (cs.CE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DB, and cs.CE, in that order.
